  <main>
    <div class="page-title">
      <h1>センター試験 文法語法クイズ 2001</h1>
      <p>空欄に入れるのに最も適当なものを一つ選べ。(全10問)</p>
    </div>

    <div class="quiz-container">

      <h2 class="quiz-section-title">2001年度 (本試験)</h2>

      <div class="quiz-question" id="q1">
        <h3>問1</h3>
        <p>If it [ 166 ] raining soon, shall we go out for a walk?</p>
        <div class="quiz-options">
          <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="1"> stopped</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="2"> stops</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="3"> will stop</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="4"> would stop</label>
        </div>
        <div class="button-wrapper single-check-wrapper"> <button class="check-single-answer-btn button">Check Answer</button> </div>
        <div class="quiz-answer" style="display: none;"> <p><strong>答え: 2. stops</strong><br>時や条件を表す副詞節 (If ...) の中では、未来のことであっても現在形を使う。</p> </div>
      </div>

      <div class="quiz-question" id="q2">
        <h3>問2</h3>
        <p>At first no one in class could find an answer, but finally David came up [ 167 ] one.</p>
        <div class="quiz-options">
          <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="1"> for</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="2"> on</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="3"> to</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="4"> with</label>
        </div>
        <div class="button-wrapper single-check-wrapper"> <button class="check-single-answer-btn button">Check Answer</button> </div>
        <div class="quiz-answer" style="display: none;"> <p><strong>答え: 4. with</strong><br>come up with ~ で「〜を思いつく」。</p> </div>
      </div>

      <div class="quiz-question" id="q3">
        <h3>問3</h3>
        <p>Jim had a skiing accident yesterday, but he's all right. He's lucky, because he [ 168 ] hurt himself badly.</p>
        <div class="quiz-options">
          <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="1"> could have</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="2"> might</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="3"> should</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="4"> will have</label>
        </div>
        <div class="button-wrapper single-check-wrapper"> <button class="check-single-answer-btn button">Check Answer</button> </div>
        <div class="quiz-answer" style="display: none;"> <p><strong>答え: 1. could have</strong><br>could have done で「〜した可能性があった（が、実際はしなかった）」。</p> </div>
      </div>

      <div class="quiz-question" id="q4">
        <h3>問4</h3>
        <p>Something's wrong with the car! We must have a [ 169 ] tire.</p>
        <div class="quiz-options">
          <label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="1"> broken</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="2"> dead</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="3"> flat</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="4"> weak</label>
        </div>
        <div class="button-wrapper single-check-wrapper"> <button class="check-single-answer-btn button">Check Answer</button> </div>
        <div class="quiz-answer" style="display: none;"> <p><strong>答え: 3. flat</strong><br>a flat tire で「パンクしたタイヤ」。</p> </div>
      </div>

      <div class="quiz-question" id="q5">
        <h3>問5</h3>
        <p>"You are coming with us to the beach on Sunday, aren't you?" "I'm really sorry, but I won't be able to [ 170 ] it after all."</p>
        <div class="quiz-options">
          <label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="1"> give</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="2"> make</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="3"> miss</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="4"> save</label>
        </div>
        <div class="button-wrapper single-check-wrapper"> <button class="check-single-answer-btn button">Check Answer</button> </div>
        <div class="quiz-answer" style="display: none;"> <p><strong>答え: 2. make</strong><br>make it で「（予定などに）間に合う、都合をつける、参加できる」。</p> </div>
      </div>

      <div class="quiz-question" id="q6">
        <h3>問6</h3>
        <p>A [ 171 ] is the money that you pay for a journey made, for example, by bus, train, or taxi.</p>
        <div class="quiz-options">
          <label><input type="radio" name="q6" value="1"> charge</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q6" value="2"> cost</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q6" value="3"> fare</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q6" value="4"> fee</label>
        </div>
        <div class="button-wrapper single-check-wrapper"> <button class="check-single-answer-btn button">Check Answer</button> </div>
        <div class="quiz-answer" style="display: none;"> <p><strong>答え: 3. fare</strong><br>バス、電車、タクシーなどの「運賃」は fare。</p> </div>
      </div>

      <div class="quiz-question" id="q7">
        <h3>問7</h3>
        <p>"Do you need that report right away?" "No, there's no hurry. Take your [ 172 ]."</p>
        <div class="quiz-options">
          <label><input type="radio" name="q7" value="1"> chance</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q7" value="2"> part</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q7" value="3"> rest</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q7" value="4"> time</label>
        </div>
        <div class="button-wrapper single-check-wrapper"> <button class="check-single-answer-btn button">Check Answer</button> </div>
        <div class="quiz-answer" style="display: none;"> <p><strong>答え: 4. time</strong><br>Take your time. で「ごゆっくりどうぞ、急がなくていいですよ」。</p> </div>
      </div>

      <div class="quiz-question" id="q8">
        <h3>問8</h3>
        <p>We [ 173 ] playing baseball for about half an hour when it started to rain heavily.</p>
        <div class="quiz-options">
          <label><input type="radio" name="q8" value="1"> had been</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q8" value="2"> have been</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q8" value="3"> might be</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q8" value="4"> would be</label>
        </div>
        <div class="button-wrapper single-check-wrapper"> <button class="check-single-answer-btn button">Check Answer</button> </div>
        <div class="quiz-answer" style="display: none;"> <p><strong>答え: 1. had been</strong><br>過去のある時点（雨が降り始めた時）まで継続していた動作を表すので、過去完了進行形を使う。</p> </div>
      </div>

      <div class="quiz-question" id="q9">
        <h3>問9</h3>
        <p>"Mom, can I use the car tonight?" "No, that's [ 174 ]. Remember what happened last time!"</p>
        <div class="quiz-options">
          <label><input type="radio" name="q9" value="1"> all the same to you</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q9" value="2"> none of your business</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q9" value="3"> out of the question</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q9" value="4"> time after time</label>
        </div>
        <div class="button-wrapper single-check-wrapper"> <button class="check-single-answer-btn button">Check Answer</button> </div>
        <div class="quiz-answer" style="display: none;"> <p><strong>答え: 3. out of the question</strong><br>out of the question で「問題外だ、不可能だ」。許可できないという強い拒絶。</p> </div>
      </div>

      <div class="quiz-question" id="q10">
        <h3>問10</h3>
        <p>"We had terrible weather during our vacation." "[ 175 ]? What a shame!"</p>
        <div class="quiz-options">
          <label><input type="radio" name="q10" value="1"> Did you</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q10" value="2"> Had it</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q10" value="3"> Was it</label>
          <label><input type="radio" name="q10" value="4"> Were you</label>
        </div>
        <div class="button-wrapper single-check-wrapper"> <button class="check-single-answer-btn button">Check Answer</button> </div>
        <div class="quiz-answer" style="display: none;"> <p><strong>答え: 1. Did you</strong><br>前の文 We had ... (過去形) を受けて「そうだったの？」と驚きや相槌を表す場合、Did you? を使う。</p> </div>
      </div>

    </div> <br>
    <p style="text-align: center;"><a href="eigo-grammar-hub.html">← 英文法一覧へ戻る</a></p>
